AH I see, we got bitten by this __pattern__ we used to do

```js
import { useState } from 'react';
// some code
// define constants
const FOO = 'foo';

const [state, setState] = useState(FOO) // initialize state 
```

This kind of pattern wants to show where to make the edits, assuming, that the reader is keeping track of some hidden code structure. In this case, that the hook is called within a function component.

